  <Instrument_Host>
    <name>Mars Global Surveyor</name>
    <type>Spacecraft</type>
    <naif_host_id>MGS</naif_host_id>
    <description>The Mars Global Surveyor (MGS) spacecraft, built by Lockheed Martin Astronautics, consisted of an equipment module housing science instruments and avionics, a propulsion module for maneuvering, solar arrays for power, and a high-gain antenna for communication. It uniquely utilized RAM instead of tape for data storage, simplifying operations. The spacecraft's attitude was precisely controlled through reaction wheels and various sensors. Data was relayed to Earth's NASA Deep Space Network (DSN), which facilitates two-way communication with deep-space missions through a global network of antennas. The DSN operates three complexes in California, Spain, and Australia, equipped with various antenna types for efficient communication with spacecraft.</description>
